tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditionally Exempt: 59th qualifier from Qualifying Tournament, Money List 61-100
tourBios.carHigh: 2012: Made the cut in 11 of 21 starts. Fired an opening round 66 at the Mylan Classic and finished the tournament T7, his best finish on the Web.com Tour. Collected his first top-10 of the year with a T7 at the Mylan Classic near Pittsburgh. Highlight of the week were back-to-back eagles in the third round at Southpointe GC. Holed a 15-foot putt for eagle at the par-5 eighth hole and then holed a pitching wedge at the par-4 ninth. 2011: Was a rookie on the Web.com Tour. Had made only four career starts prior to the beginning of the season. Was T30 at the Utah Championship. 2010: Only prior experience on the PGA TOUR came at the Reno-Tahoe Open, where he missed the cut.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Three-time Southwestern League first-team member at Temecula Valley High School...Won five events in college, 2010 first-team All American, 2010 Palmer Cup member, Three-time Big West Conference Player of the Year and Big West Freshman of the Year.
tourBios.personal: Plays lefthanded...Golf instructors include Don Brown and Randy Wood...Biggest thrill in golf is getting the call for being on the Palmer Cup...Favorite course he has played in Riviera CC...Always marks his ball with a quarter from the 1960s...Favorite websites are facebook.com, espn.com and weatherchannel.com...Favorite pro team is the Los Angeles Lakers...Favorite TV show is "The Simpsons." Favorite movies are anyting with Denzel Washington. Favorite entertainers are Kanye West and Eminem. Favorite book is Golf is Not a Game of Perfect. Favorite athlete to watch is Kobe Bryant...Keeps almonds and beef jerky in his golf bag for a snack...Dream foursome includes Bubba Watson, Lee Trevino and David Feherty...Favorite quote is "Our best is better than the rest."

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T7th in 2012 at the Mylan Classic.
